23// Sets the embedder fields to 0 for a TypedArray which is under construction.
24void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::SetupTypedArrayEmbedderFields(
25 TNode<JSTypedArray> holder) {
26 InitializeJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsCppHeapWrapperPtr(holder);
27 for (int offset = JSTypedArray::kHeaderSize;
28 offset < JSTypedArray::kSizeWithEmbedderFields; offset += kTaggedSize) {
29 // TODO(v8:10391, saelo): Handle external pointers in EmbedderDataSlot
30 StoreObjectField(holder, offset, SmiConstant(0));
31 }
32}
33
34// Allocate a new ArrayBuffer and initialize it with empty properties and
35// elements.
36// TODO(bmeurer,v8:4153): Rename this and maybe fix up the implementation a bit.
37TNode<JSArrayBuffer> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::AllocateEmptyOnHeapBuffer(
38 TNode<Context> context) {
39 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
40 TNode<Map> map =
41 CAST(LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::ARRAY_BUFFER_MAP_INDEX));
42 TNode<FixedArray> empty_fixed_array = EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
43
44 TNode<JSArrayBuffer> buffer = UncheckedCast<JSArrayBuffer>(
45 Allocate(JSArrayBuffer::kSizeWithEmbedderFields));
46 StoreMapNoWriteBarrier(buffer, map);
47 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArray::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
48 empty_fixed_array);
49 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArray::kElementsOffset,
50 empty_fixed_array);
51 // Setup the ArrayBuffer.
52 // - Set BitField to 0.
53 // - Set IsExternal and IsDetachable bits of BitFieldSlot.
54 // - Set the byte_length field to zero.
55 // - Set backing_store to null/Tagged<Smi>(0).
56 // - Set extension to null.
57 // - Set all embedder fields to Tagged<Smi>(0).
58 if (FIELD_SIZE(JSArrayBuffer::kOptionalPaddingOffset) != 0) {
59 DCHECK_EQ(4, FIELD_SIZE(JSArrayBuffer::kOptionalPaddingOffset));
60 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(
61 buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kOptionalPaddingOffset, Int32Constant(0));
62 }
63 int32_t bitfield_value = (1 << JSArrayBuffer::IsExternalBit::kShift) |
64 (1 << JSArrayBuffer::IsDetachableBit::kShift);
65 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kBitFieldOffset,
66 Int32Constant(bitfield_value));
67
68 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kDetachKeyOffset,
69 UndefinedConstant());
70 StoreBoundedSizeToObject(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kRawByteLengthOffset,
71 UintPtrConstant(0));
72 StoreSandboxedPointerToObject(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kBackingStoreOffset,
73 EmptyBackingStoreBufferConstant());
74#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
75 // When pointer compression is enabled, the extension slot contains a
76 // (lazily-initialized) external pointer handle.
77 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kExtensionOffset,
78 ExternalPointerHandleNullConstant());
79#else
80 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, JSArrayBuffer::kExtensionOffset,
81 IntPtrConstant(0));
82#endif
83 InitializeJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsCppHeapWrapperPtr(buffer);
84 for (int offset = JSArrayBuffer::kHeaderSize;
85 offset < JSArrayBuffer::kSizeWithEmbedderFields; offset += kTaggedSize) {
86 // TODO(v8:10391, saelo): Handle external pointers in EmbedderDataSlot
87 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(buffer, offset, SmiConstant(0));
88 }
89 return buffer;
90}

94 ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kConstructAbstractClass,
95 "TypedArray");

98// ES #sec-typedarray-constructors
99TF_BUILTIN(TypedArrayConstructor, TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler) {
100 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
101 auto target = Parameter<JSFunction>(Descriptor::kJSTarget);
102 auto new_target = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kJSNewTarget);
103 TNode<IntPtrT> argc = ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
104 UncheckedParameter<Int32T>(Descriptor::kJSActualArgumentsCount));
105 CodeStubArguments args(this, argc);
106 TNode<Object> arg1 = args.GetOptionalArgumentValue(0);
107 TNode<Object> arg2 = args.GetOptionalArgumentValue(1);
108 TNode<Object> arg3 = args.GetOptionalArgumentValue(2);
109
110 // If NewTarget is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
111 // All the TypedArray constructors have this as the first step:
112 // https://tc39.github.io/ecma262/#sec-typedarray-constructors
113 Label throwtypeerror(this, Label::kDeferred);
114 GotoIf(IsUndefined(new_target), &throwtypeerror);
115
116 TNode<Object> result = CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCreateTypedArray, context,
117 target, new_target, arg1, arg2, arg3);
118 args.PopAndReturn(result);
119
120 BIND(&throwtypeerror);
121 {
122 TNode<String> name =
123 CAST(CallRuntime(Runtime::kGetFunctionName, context, target));
124 ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kConstructorNotFunction, name);
125 }
126}

128// ES6 #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype.bytelength
129TF_BUILTIN(TypedArrayPrototypeByteLength, TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler) {
130 const char* const kMethodName = "get TypedArray.prototype.byteLength";
131 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
132 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
133
134 // Check if the {receiver} is actually a JSTypedArray.
135 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, receiver, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, kMethodName);
136
137 TNode<JSTypedArray> receiver_array = CAST(receiver);
138 TNode<JSArrayBuffer> receiver_buffer =
139 LoadJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(receiver_array);
140
141 Label variable_length(this), normal(this);
142 Branch(IsVariableLengthJSArrayBufferView(receiver_array), &variable_length,
143 &normal);
144 BIND(&variable_length);
145 {
146 Return(ChangeUintPtrToTagged(LoadVariableLengthJSTypedArrayByteLength(
147 context, receiver_array, receiver_buffer)));
148 }
149
150 BIND(&normal);
151 {
152 // Default to zero if the {receiver}s buffer was detached.
153 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length = Select<UintPtrT>(
154 IsDetachedBuffer(receiver_buffer), [=] { return UintPtrConstant(0); },
155 [=] { return LoadJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(receiver_array); });
156 Return(ChangeUintPtrToTagged(byte_length));
157 }
158}

160// ES6 #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype.byteoffset
161TF_BUILTIN(TypedArrayPrototypeByteOffset, TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler) {
162 const char* const kMethodName = "get TypedArray.prototype.byteOffset";
163 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
164 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
165
166 // Check if the {receiver} is actually a JSTypedArray.
167 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, receiver, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, kMethodName);
168
169 // Default to zero if the {receiver}s buffer was detached / out of bounds.
170 Label detached_or_oob(this), not_detached_nor_oob(this);
171 IsJSArrayBufferViewDetachedOrOutOfBounds(CAST(receiver), &detached_or_oob,
172 &not_detached_nor_oob);
173 BIND(&detached_or_oob);
174 Return(ChangeUintPtrToTagged(UintPtrConstant(0)));
175
176 BIND(&not_detached_nor_oob);
177 Return(
178 ChangeUintPtrToTagged(LoadJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(CAST(receiver))));
179}

181// ES6 #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype.length
182TF_BUILTIN(TypedArrayPrototypeLength, TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler) {
183 const char* const kMethodName = "get TypedArray.prototype.length";
184 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
185 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
186
187 // Check if the {receiver} is actually a JSTypedArray.
188 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, receiver, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, kMethodName);
189
190 TNode<JSTypedArray> receiver_array = CAST(receiver);
191 TVARIABLE(UintPtrT, length);
192 Label detached(this), end(this);
193 length = LoadJSTypedArrayLengthAndCheckDetached(receiver_array, &detached);
194 Return(ChangeUintPtrToTagged(length.value()));
195 BIND(&detached);
196 Return(ChangeUintPtrToTagged(UintPtrConstant(0)));
197}

199TNode<BoolT> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::IsUint8ElementsKind(
200 TNode<Int32T> kind) {
201 return Word32Or(
202 Word32Or(Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(UINT8_ELEMENTS)),
203 Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS))),
204 Word32Or(
205 Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(RAB_GSAB_UINT8_ELEMENTS)),
206 Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(RAB_GSAB_UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS))));
207}
208
209TNode<BoolT> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::IsBigInt64ElementsKind(
210 TNode<Int32T> kind) {
211 static_assert(BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS + 1 == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS);
212 return Word32Or(
213 IsElementsKindInRange(kind, BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, BIGINT64_ELEMENTS),
214 IsElementsKindInRange(kind, RAB_GSAB_BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS,
215 RAB_GSAB_BIGINT64_ELEMENTS));
216}

218TNode<IntPtrT> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::GetTypedArrayElementSize(
219 TNode<Int32T> elements_kind) {
220 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, element_size);
221
222 DispatchTypedArrayByElementsKind(
223 elements_kind,
224 [&](ElementsKind el_kind, int size, int typed_array_fun_index) {
225 element_size = IntPtrConstant(size);
226 });
227
228 return element_size.value();
229}

237TorqueStructTypedArrayElementsInfo
238TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::GetTypedArrayElementsInfo(TNode<Map> map) {
239 TNode<Int32T> elements_kind = LoadMapElementsKind(map);
240 TVARIABLE(UintPtrT, var_size_log2);
241 TVARIABLE(Map, var_map);
242 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
243
244 DispatchTypedArrayByElementsKind(
245 elements_kind,
246 [&](ElementsKind kind, int size, int typed_array_fun_index) {
247 DCHECK_GT(size, 0);
248 var_size_log2 = UintPtrConstant(ElementsKindToShiftSize(kind));
249 });
250
251 return TorqueStructTypedArrayElementsInfo{var_size_log2.value(),
252 elements_kind};
253}

255TNode<JSFunction> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::GetDefaultConstructor(
256 TNode<Context> context, TNode<JSTypedArray> exemplar) {
257 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, context_slot);
258 TNode<Int32T> elements_kind = LoadElementsKind(exemplar);
259
260 DispatchTypedArrayByElementsKind(
261 elements_kind,
262 [&](ElementsKind el_kind, int size, int typed_array_function_index) {
263 context_slot = IntPtrConstant(typed_array_function_index);
264 });
265
266 return CAST(
267 LoadContextElement(LoadNativeContext(context), context_slot.value()));
268}

270TNode<JSTypedArray> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::ValidateTypedArray(
271 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> obj, const char* method_name) {
272 // If it is not a typed array, throw
273 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, obj, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, method_name);
274
275 // If the typed array's buffer is detached, throw
276 ThrowIfArrayBufferViewBufferIsDetached(context, CAST(obj), method_name);
277
278 // TODO(v8:11111): Throw if the RAB / GSAB is OOB.
279 return CAST(obj);
280}
281
282TNode<UintPtrT> TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::ValidateTypedArrayAndGetLength(
283 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> obj, const char* method_name) {
284 // If it is not a typed array, throw
285 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, obj, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, method_name);
286
287 Label detached_or_oob(this), not_detached_nor_oob(this);
288 TNode<UintPtrT> length =
289 LoadJSTypedArrayLengthAndCheckDetached(CAST(obj), &detached_or_oob);
290 Goto(&not_detached_nor_oob);
291
292 BIND(&detached_or_oob);
293 ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kDetachedOperation, method_name);
294
295 BIND(&not_detached_nor_oob);
296 return length;
297}

394void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::DispatchTypedArrayByElementsKind(
395 TNode<Word32T> elements_kind, const TypedArraySwitchCase& case_function) {
396 Label next(this), if_unknown_type(this, Label::kDeferred);
397
398 int32_t elements_kinds[] = {
399#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) TYPE##_ELEMENTS,
400 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE) RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
401#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
402 };
403
404#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) Label if_##type##array(this);
405 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
406 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
407#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
408
409 Label* elements_kind_labels[] = {
410#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) &if_##type##array,
411 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE) RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
412#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
413 };
414 static_assert(arraysize(elements_kinds) == arraysize(elements_kind_labels));
415
416 Switch(elements_kind, &if_unknown_type, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
417 arraysize(elements_kinds));
418
419#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
420 BIND(&if_##type##array); \
421 { \
422 case_function(TYPE##_ELEMENTS, sizeof(ctype), \
423 Context::TYPE##_ARRAY_FUN_INDEX); \
424 Goto(&next); \
425 }
426 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
427#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
428
429#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype, NON_RAB_GSAB_TYPE) \
430 BIND(&if_##type##array); \
431 { \
432 case_function(TYPE##_ELEMENTS, sizeof(ctype), \
433 Context::NON_RAB_GSAB_TYPE##_ARRAY_FUN_INDEX); \
434 Goto(&next); \
435 }
436 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS_WITH_NON_RAB_GSAB_ELEMENTS_KIND(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
437#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
438
439 BIND(&if_unknown_type);
440 Unreachable();
441
442 BIND(&next);
443}

445void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::SetJSTypedArrayOnHeapDataPtr(
446 TNode<JSTypedArray> holder, TNode<ByteArray> base, TNode<UintPtrT> offset) {
447 offset = UintPtrAdd(UintPtrConstant(ByteArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag),
448 offset);
449 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
450 TNode<IntPtrT> full_base = Signed(BitcastTaggedToWord(base));
451 TNode<Int32T> compressed_base = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(full_base);
452 // TODO(v8:9706): Add a way to directly use kRootRegister value.
453 TNode<IntPtrT> ptr_compr_cage_base =
454 IntPtrSub(full_base, Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(compressed_base)));
455 // Add JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray() to offset.
456 // See JSTypedArray::AddExternalPointerCompensationForDeserialization().
457 DCHECK_EQ(
458 isolate()->cage_base(),
459 JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray(isolate()));
460 offset = Unsigned(IntPtrAdd(offset, ptr_compr_cage_base));
461 }
462
463 StoreJSTypedArrayBasePointer(holder, base);
464 StoreJSTypedArrayExternalPointerPtr(holder, ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(offset));
465}
466
467void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::SetJSTypedArrayOffHeapDataPtr(
468 TNode<JSTypedArray> holder, TNode<RawPtrT> base, TNode<UintPtrT> offset) {
469 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(holder, JSTypedArray::kBasePointerOffset,
470 SmiConstant(0));
471
472 base = RawPtrAdd(base, Signed(offset));
473 StoreJSTypedArrayExternalPointerPtr(holder, base);
474}

476void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromNumeric(
477 TNode<Context> context, TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array,
478 TNode<UintPtrT> index, TNode<Numeric> value, ElementsKind elements_kind) {
479 TNode<RawPtrT> data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(typed_array);
480 switch (elements_kind) {
481 case UINT8_ELEMENTS:
482 case UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS:
483 case INT8_ELEMENTS:
484 case UINT16_ELEMENTS:
485 case INT16_ELEMENTS:
486 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index, SmiToInt32(CAST(value)));
487 break;
488 case UINT32_ELEMENTS:
489 case INT32_ELEMENTS:
490 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index,
491 TruncateTaggedToWord32(context, value));
492 break;
493 case FLOAT16_ELEMENTS:
494 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index,
495 TruncateFloat64ToFloat16(LoadHeapNumberValue(CAST(value))));
496 break;
497 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
498 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index,
499 TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(LoadHeapNumberValue(CAST(value))));
500 break;
501 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
502 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index,
503 LoadHeapNumberValue(CAST(value)));
504 break;
505 case BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS:
506 case BIGINT64_ELEMENTS:
507 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index,
508 UncheckedCast<BigInt>(value));
509 break;
510 default:
511 UNREACHABLE();
512 }
513}
514
515template <typename TValue>
516void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(
517 TNode<Context> context, TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array,
518 TNode<UintPtrT> index, TNode<TValue> prepared_value,
519 ElementsKind elements_kind, Label* if_detached_or_out_of_bounds) {
520 static_assert(std::is_same<TValue, Word32T>::value ||
521 std::is_same<TValue, Float16T>::value ||
522 std::is_same<TValue, Float32T>::value ||
523 std::is_same<TValue, Float64T>::value ||
524 std::is_same<TValue, BigInt>::value,
525 "Only Word32T, Float16T, Float32T, Float64T or BigInt values "
526 "are allowed");
527 // ToNumber/ToBigInt (or other functions called by the upper level) may
528 // execute JavaScript code, which could detach the TypedArray's buffer or make
529 // the TypedArray out of bounds.
530 TNode<UintPtrT> length = LoadJSTypedArrayLengthAndCheckDetached(
531 typed_array, if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
532 GotoIf(UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(index, length),
533 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
534
535 TNode<RawPtrT> data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(typed_array);
536 StoreElement(data_ptr, elements_kind, index, prepared_value);
537}
538
539void TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler::StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromTagged(
540 TNode<Context> context, TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array,
541 TNode<UintPtrT> index, TNode<Object> value, ElementsKind elements_kind,
542 Label* if_detached_or_out_of_bounds) {
543 switch (elements_kind) {
544 case UINT8_ELEMENTS:
545 case INT8_ELEMENTS:
546 case UINT16_ELEMENTS:
547 case INT16_ELEMENTS:
548 case UINT32_ELEMENTS:
549 case INT32_ELEMENTS:
550 case UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS: {
551 auto prepared_value = PrepareValueForWriteToTypedArray<Word32T>(
552 value, elements_kind, context);
553 StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(context, typed_array, index,
554 prepared_value, elements_kind,
555 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
556 break;
557 }
558 case FLOAT16_ELEMENTS: {
559 auto prepared_value = PrepareValueForWriteToTypedArray<Float16T>(
560 value, elements_kind, context);
561 StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(context, typed_array, index,
562 prepared_value, elements_kind,
563 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
564 break;
565 }
566 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS: {
567 auto prepared_value = PrepareValueForWriteToTypedArray<Float32T>(
568 value, elements_kind, context);
569 StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(context, typed_array, index,
570 prepared_value, elements_kind,
571 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
572 break;
573 }
574 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS: {
575 auto prepared_value = PrepareValueForWriteToTypedArray<Float64T>(
576 value, elements_kind, context);
577 StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(context, typed_array, index,
578 prepared_value, elements_kind,
579 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
580 break;
581 }
582 case BIGINT64_ELEMENTS:
583 case BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS: {
584 auto prepared_value = PrepareValueForWriteToTypedArray<BigInt>(
585 value, elements_kind, context);
586 StoreJSTypedArrayElementFromPreparedValue(context, typed_array, index,
587 prepared_value, elements_kind,
588 if_detached_or_out_of_bounds);
589 break;
590 }
591 default:
592 UNREACHABLE();
593 }

595
596// ES #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype-@@tostringtag
597TF_BUILTIN(TypedArrayPrototypeToStringTag, TypedArrayBuiltinsAssembler) {
598 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
599 Label if_receiverisheapobject(this), return_undefined(this);
600 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(receiver), &return_undefined, &if_receiverisheapobject);
601
602 // Dispatch on the elements kind, offset by
603 // FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND.
604 static_assert(LAST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1 ==
605 FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND);
606 size_t const kTypedElementsKindCount =
607 LAST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND -
608 FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1;
609#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
610 Label return_##type##array(this); \
611 BIND(&return_##type##array); \
612 Return(StringConstant(#Type "Array"));
613 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
614#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
615
616 // clang-format off
617 Label* elements_kind_labels[kTypedElementsKindCount] = {
618 // The TYPED_ARRAYS macro is invoked twice because while the RAB/GSAB-backed
619 // TAs have distinct ElementsKinds internally, they have the same "class"
620 // name for toString output.
621#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) &return_##type##array,
622 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
623 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
624#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
625 };
626
627 int32_t elements_kinds[kTypedElementsKindCount] = {
628#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
629 TYPE##_ELEMENTS - FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND,
630 // The use of FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND below is not a typo! This
631 // computes an index into elements_kind_labels, and all TypedArray
632 // ElementsKind values are contiguous.
633#define RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
634 TYPE##_ELEMENTS - FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND,
635 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
636 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
637#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
638#undef RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
639 };
640 // clang-format on
641
642 // We offset the dispatch by FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND, so that
643 // this can be turned into a non-sparse table switch for ideal performance.
644 BIND(&if_receiverisheapobject);
645 TNode<HeapObject> receiver_heap_object = CAST(receiver);
646 TNode<Int32T> elements_kind =
647 Int32Sub(LoadElementsKind(receiver_heap_object),
648 Int32Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND));
649 Switch(elements_kind, &return_undefined, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
650 kTypedElementsKindCount);
651
652 BIND(&return_undefined);
653 Return(UndefinedConstant());
654}
